<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>

<Fragment slot="head-scripts">
  {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}
</Fragment>

<CommercialHero
  eyebrow="ITW Food Equipment Group · Troy, Ohio · Legacy Series Planetary · HL120 to HL1400 · 20 to 30+ Year Service Life"
  title="Hobart Mixer Repair Los Angeles"
  subtitle={`Hobart Legacy series planetary mixers HL120 through HL1400 across LA, OC, Ventura. Bowl-lift OSHA compliance, gear transmission rebuild, motor service. ${phone}`}
  heroImageTitle="Hobart Legacy Mixer Repair"
  showBranches={true}
/>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Hobart Legacy service</p>
    <h2>The cast-iron gear transmission that outlasts the bakery cabinet.</h2>
    <p>Hobart Legacy series planetary mixers dominate the US commercial mixer market across LA-area bakeries, pizzerias, restaurants, school cafeterias, and institutional kitchens. Hobart is part of ITW Food Equipment Group, with manufacturing in Troy, Ohio. Sister brands include Vulcan, Stero, Baxter, and Traulsen. The Legacy series cast-iron gear transmission is the cornerstone of Hobart mixer reputation: 20 to 30+ year service life is normal with periodic component replacement.</p>
    <p>We service the full Legacy family across all five SoCal counties. <strong>HL120</strong> (12 quart, smallest commercial), <strong>HL200</strong> (20 quart, common in pizzerias and small bakeries), <strong>HL400</strong> (40 quart, full-service bakery workhorse), <strong>HL600</strong> (60 quart, high-volume bakery and school cafeteria), <strong>HL800</strong> (80 quart, institutional), <strong>HL1400</strong> (140 quart, large institutional and wholesale). Plus heritage Legacy units from the 1990s still in active service.</p>
    <p>Service scope: bowl-lift OSHA-compliant safety interlocks, planetary drive motor, separate bowl-lift motor (HL200 and larger have distinct motors for planetary drive vs bowl lift), cast-iron gear transmission rebuild and oil seal replacement, contactor and capacitor service, on/off switch replacement, attachment service. OEM Hobart parts via ITW Food Equipment authorized distribution.</p>
    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573 license. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. BBB Accredited. Phones answered 24/7. <a href="/credentials/licensed/">License verifiable.</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Legacy lineup</p>
    <h2>The Hobart Legacy family by capacity and application.</h2>
    <p class="lead">Hobart maintains clear capacity tiers across the Legacy series. All share cast-iron gear transmission architecture, OSHA-compliant bowl-lift interlock design, and benefit from the ITW Food Equipment parts network.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">HL120 (12 quart, smallest commercial)</h3>
    <p>Mid-size bakery, pizzeria, and prep kitchen applications. Single motor architecture (bowl raises by hand mechanism, no separate bowl-lift motor). Standard service items: motor, contactor, gearbox.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">HL200 (20 quart, full-service workhorse)</h3>
    <p>Most common Hobart Legacy size in LA. Pizzerias, mid-volume bakeries, restaurant prep kitchens. Separate bowl-lift motor (distinct from planetary drive). OSHA-compliant safety interlock at bowl cradle.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">HL400 (40 quart, bakery workhorse)</h3>
    <p>Full-service bakery standard. Heavy-duty cast-iron gear transmission with multi-speed selection. The Legacy unit most commonly serviced for gear transmission oil seal at year 8 to 12 typical.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">HL600 (60 quart, high-volume institutional)</h3>
    <p>School cafeterias, university dining, hospital food service, large bakeries. Heavier-duty drive train than HL400. Same OSHA bowl-lift architecture.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">HL800 / HL1400 (80, 140 quart, institutional)</h3>
    <p>Large institutional applications: wholesale bakeries, school district central kitchens, hospital food service operations at scale. Heaviest gear transmission, separate bowl-lift motor. Service work requires forklift access for major component swaps.</p>
    <h3 class="series-h3">Heritage Legacy (pre-2000)</h3>
    <p>1990s and earlier Legacy units still in active service. Most parts available through ITW; some vintage components require aftermarket cross-reference. Heritage refurbishment is specialty work that few LA shops handle; we do.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Common scenarios</p>
    <h2>Top Hobart Legacy service items in our 5-county territory.</h2>
    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Bowl-lift safety interlock (OSHA-critical).</strong> Year 5 to 9 typical. Failed interlock means mixer runs with bowl lowered, OSHA pinch-point citation. $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor contactor or capacitor.</strong> Year 6 to 10. Mixer won't start. $200 to $360.</li>
      <li><strong>Bowl-lift motor (HL200 and larger).</strong> Year 8 to 12. Bowl won't lift or lifts erratically. $580 to $880.</li>
      <li><strong>Gear transmission oil seal.</strong> Caught at seal stage: $440 to $720 with oil refill. Run to gear damage: $1,400 to $2,400 rebuild.</li>
      <li><strong>Planetary drive motor.</strong> Year 12 to 15+ heavy use. $880 to $1,400.</li>
      <li><strong>On/off switch wear.</strong> Year 8 to 12. $140 to $260.</li>
      <li><strong>Heritage Legacy refurbishment.</strong> Multi-component on 1990s and earlier units. $1,800 to $3,400.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>
    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Bakery in Pasadena · Hobart HL400 (12 years)</h3>
        <p>Bowl-lift safety interlock flagged at health inspection plus gear transmission oil seep. Replaced interlock plus oil seal preventively (avoiding cascading damage). Total: $980. OSHA documentation provided.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Pizzeria in West Hollywood · Hobart HL200 (8 years)</h3>
        <p>Won't start. Diagnosed: motor contactor degraded. Replaced contactor plus tested through full duty cycle. Total: $360.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>School cafeteria in Long Beach · Hobart HL600 (15 years)</h3>
        <p>Bowl-lift motor failed. Replaced bowl-lift motor (separate from planetary drive on HL600). Tested through full lift cycle plus interlock verification. Total: $880.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Bakery in Calabasas · Hobart HL400 (18 years)</h3>
        <p>Gear transmission running progressively dry; operator had reported slight leak 2 months prior. Caught after gear teeth showed wear but before catastrophic failure. Rebuilt gear transmission on-site. Total: $1,840.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Heritage bakery in Los Angeles · Hobart HL400 (1990s, 28 years)</h3>
        <p>Multi-component refurbishment: motor bearing service, bowl-lift motor replacement, gear transmission oil seal, on/off switch, contactor. Total: $2,640. Owner happy to keep the original cast-iron base running.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2>What we do for Hobart Legacy mixers, and what we don't.</h2>
    <p><strong>We service:</strong> Hobart Legacy HL120, HL200, HL400, HL600, HL800, HL1400 plus heritage Legacy from the 1990s. Bowl-lift OSHA-compliant safety interlocks, planetary drive motors, separate bowl-lift motors, cast-iron gear transmission rebuild and oil seal replacement, contactors, capacitors, on/off switches, attachment service.</p>
    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> spiral mixer reverse-rotation conversion (specialty modification); industrial dough-mixing systems for large-scale wholesale bakeries (specialty industrial trade); Hobart factory rebuild service when cabinet condition warrants depot-level work (we refer). Sister ITW brands (Vulcan, Stero, Baxter, Traulsen) covered on their own service lines.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Pricing</p>
    <h2>Hobart Legacy mixer repair costs.</h2>
    <p class="lead">Diagnostic is $120 (commercial tier), waived with repair. OEM Hobart parts via ITW Food Equipment authorized distribution.</p>
    <table class="price-table">
