<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Why operators choose us for Hobart</p>
    <h2>What separates our Hobart Legacy service from generalist commercial repair.</h2>
    <ul class="reasons-list">
      <li><strong>ITW Food Equipment parts network access.</strong> 5 to 7 day standard ship for most Legacy service items.</li>
      <li><strong>OSHA bowl-lift safety interlock expertise.</strong> Most common compliance failure point on commercial mixers; we service correctly with documentation.</li>
      <li><strong>Cast-iron gear transmission rebuild capability.</strong> Many LA shops refer Legacy gearbox work out; we rebuild on-site when cabinet condition warrants.</li>
      <li><strong>Heritage Legacy vintage service.</strong> 1990s and earlier units serviceable; few LA shops handle vintage refurbishment.</li>
      <li><strong>Oil seal preventive repair.</strong> Catching gear transmission oil leak at seal stage saves $1,400+ vs run-to-failure rebuild.</li>
      <li><strong>HL120 through HL1400 coverage.</strong> All six current sizes plus heritage Legacy serviceable.</li>
      <li><strong>Sister ITW brand coordination.</strong> Hobart slicer plus Vulcan range plus Traulsen reach-in single-dispatch coordination across the ITW family.</li>
      <li><strong>BHGS #A49573 plus EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.</strong> Verifiable.</li>
      <li><strong>24/7 phone answering.</strong></li>
      <li><strong>Same-day across LA, OC, Ventura.</strong></li>
    </ul>
